humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions that there are 21 positive lymph nodes out of 24 assessed lymph nodes (pN3a) in the left axillary lymph nodes. This corresponds to N3 stage as per the AJCC staging system.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage is determined by the number of lymph nodes involved. In this report, metastatic carcinoma was found in 21 out of 24 lymph nodes (pN3a). This indicates that the patient's cancer has spread to a significant number of lymph nodes, classifying it as N3.
